Legendary jazz musician Hugh Masekela has died. Masekela passed away at a Johannesburg hospital on Tuesday morning after announcing in 2017 that he had prostate cancer. He died at age 78. Masekela performed with several well-known artists such as Miriam Makeba and Thandiswa Mazwai, among others. Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa paid tribute to Masekela via his Twitter account following the news of his passing. A baobab tree has fallen, the nation has lost a one of a kind musician with the passing of Jazz legend bra Hugh Masekela. We can safely say bra Hugh was one of the great architects of Afro-Jazz and he uplifted the soul of our nation through his timeless music. #RIPBraHughMasekelapic.twitter.com/JVy47GA6aU — Min. Nathi Mthethwa (@NathiMthethwaSA) January 23, 2018 -TNA Reporter